The article discusses the 45th annual March for Life, which is the world's largest annual pro-life rally. The event, organized by the March for Life Education and Defense Fund, aims to promote the value and protection of every human life. The article mentions the significant growth in support for the cause over the years, with an estimated turnout of 650,000 in 2013. President Donald Trump and Vice President Mike Pence showed their support for the event via video satellite and proclaimed January 22, 2018, as National Sanctity of Human Life Day. The Trump Administration has been actively working to change the conversation and policies surrounding abortion, including overturning an Obama Administration rule that prohibited states from defunding abortion service providers. The article emphasizes the power of a positive pro-life message in addressing a challenging subject.